    "plan_cost_usd": 1.1147520999999998,
    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written:\n\n## Plan: Add `Bun.INI` Public API\n\n**5 files to touch:**\n\n### 1. CREATE `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`\nA self-contained INI parser/stringifier modelled after `JSON5Object.zig`:\n- **`create()`** — returns a JS object with `parse` and `stringify` functions\n- **`parse()`** — line-by-line parser: skips blank lines and `;`/`#` comments, `[section]` headers become nested JS objects, `key = value` pairs set string properties; throws `SyntaxError` on malformed input\n- **`stringify()`** — top-level primitives emitted first as `key = value`, then nested objects as `[section]` blocks; throws if objects are nested >1 level deep\n\n### 2. MODIFY `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` (4 spots)\n- Add `pub const INI = toJSLazyPropertyCallback(Bun.getINIObject);` in the lazy-property const block (~line 70)\n- Add `@export(&BunObject.INI, ...)` in the exports block (~line 140)\n- Add `pub fn getINIObject(...)` getter function after `getYAMLObject` (~line 1289)\n- Add `const INIObject = bun.api.INIObject;` import alias (~line 2083)\n\n### 3. MODIFY `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h`\nAdd `macro(INI) \\` alphabetically between `Glob` and `JSON5` in `FOR_EACH_GETTER`.\n\n### 4. MODIFY `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp`\nAdd `INI  BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI  DontDelete|PropertyCallback` to `bunObjectTable` between the JSON5 and JSONL rows.\n\n### 5. MODIFY `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts`\nAdd a `namespace INI { parse(...): Record<string,any>; stringify(...): string; }` block with JSDoc examples, inserted after `namespace TOML`.",
